# VPS deployment (template)

Copy this file to `infra/DEPLOY.local.md` (gitignored) and fill in your own values. **Do not commit** `DEPLOY.local.md`.

This repository runs **backend + static frontend only** (nginx in the `web` image serves the SPA — **no** API reverse proxy and **no** certbot). **TLS and certbot** live in a separate repository; there you point `aero.draxnor.com` (or your domain) and `proxy_pass` to the ports below.

## Requirements

- VPS with Docker and Docker Compose v2
- Application repo e.g. under `/opt/aero-gemini`
- Edge configuration (nginx + certbot) on the same host or in a container

## 1. DNS and firewall

1. **A** / **AAAA** record for your domain → VPS public IP (handled by edge nginx from the other repo).
2. Firewall: from the internet only edge ports should be open (usually **80** and **443**). Ports **8080** and **8000** in `docker-compose.prod.yml` bind to **127.0.0.1** — they are not exposed publicly.

## 2. Environment configuration

1. `cp infra/.env.example infra/.env`
2. Set at least **`AERO_JWT_SECRET`**, **`AERO_DATABASE_URL`** (e.g. `sqlite:////app/data/aero.db` with volume `backend_data`).

The frontend is built with **`VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api`** — the browser calls the API on the **same host as the page**; edge nginx must forward `/api` to the backend (e.g. `proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000;` preserving URIs starting with `/api`).

## 3. Starting the application stack

From the **repository root**:

```bash
docker compose -p aero-prod --env-file infra/.env -f infra/docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build
```

### Seed database (`seed.py`)

The API does **not** create users on startup. Run the seed once (idempotent) so demo accounts exist — from the **repository root**.

Ready-made helpers (permission fix + seed + inspect): **`infra/scripts/`** (`fix-backend-volume-permissions.*`, `run-seed-in-docker.*`, `inspect-backend-data-permissions.sh`).

**Option A — `uv` on the host** (same machine as the repo, same `AERO_DATABASE_URL` as in `infra/.env`; use when the DB file is reachable from the host, e.g. local SQLite path):

```bash
set -a && source infra/.env && set +a   # bash: load env
uv run --directory backend python seed.py
```

**Option B — one-off backend container** (SQLite only inside the `backend_data` volume; run on the VPS from repo root after `docker compose up`):

```bash
docker compose -p aero-prod --env-file infra/.env -f infra/docker-compose.prod.yml run --rm \
  -v aero-prod_backend_data:/app/data \
  -v "$(pwd)/backend:/workspace/backend:ro" \
  --workdir /workspace/backend \
  aero-backend \
  python seed.py
```

The backend image entrypoint (`chown` on `/app/data`, then `runuser` as `appuser`) exists so SQLite on a Docker **named volume** is writable. If you still see `PermissionError` on `/app/data`, rebuild and restart the stack (`up -d --build`), then run Option B again.

`SEED_PROFILE` in `infra/.env` may be `minimal` or `full` (default `full`). See `backend/seed.py` for seeded users and passwords.

After startup (default `127.0.0.1` binding):

| Service  | URL for edge nginx on the host |
|----------|--------------------------------|
| Frontend | `http://127.0.0.1:8080`        |
| Backend  | `http://127.0.0.1:8000`        |

Example snippets for **edge nginx** (adjust TLS file paths in your repo):

- `location /api` → `proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000;` plus headers `Host`, `X-Forwarded-For`, `X-Forwarded-Proto`.
- `location /` → `proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8080;` (upstream is unprivileged nginx on **8080** inside the container — on a shared Docker network use `http://aero-web:8080` instead).

### Edge nginx in Docker (instead of on the host)

Then `127.0.0.1` inside the edge container is **not** the host. Options: **(a)** shared Docker network (`external: true`) and `proxy_pass http://aero-web:8080` / `http://aero-backend:8000` — attach both stacks to the same network (see `docker-compose.prod.yml`); **(b)** on Linux, `extra_hosts: ["host.docker.internal:host-gateway"]` and proxy to `http://host.docker.internal:8080`, etc.

## 4. TLS and certbot

Do this **in the edge nginx repository** (webroot, reverse proxy, certificate renewal).

## 5. Updating the application

```bash
cd YOUR_REPO_PATH
git pull
docker compose -p aero-prod --env-file infra/.env -f infra/docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build
```

## 6. Database backup

```bash
docker run --rm -v aero-prod_backend_data:/data -v $(pwd):/backup alpine tar czf /backup/backend_data.tgz -C /data .
```

(`-p` must match the one used with `docker compose up`.)
